                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>Students can look to Joey McMahon and his organization for inspiration, said Duke junior Kaushik Sahoo, who has worked on the Monday Life team for two years and is currently its head of technology. <br></p>
<p>“This biggest thing I think Duke students can learn from Joey McMahon is that everyone should not only pursue their passions, but use whatever resources they have available to better society,” Sahoo said. </p>
<p>McMahon himself has some words of advice for college students. He believes that undergraduates should both use their particular skill sets to solve pertinent social problems and learn to love Mondays.</p>
<br>
